 Fine Print				 				 				 																Big fat star																																	 Athens, Oct. 13 (AP): Actress Nia Vardalos, star of My Big Fat Greek Wedding, stood under a big reflector today, filming a new romantic comedy among the dramatic ruins on the Acropolis.																																	The scene will appear in My Life in Ruins, also starring Richard Dreyfuss, and follows a decision by Greek authorities to relax a long-standing ban on any commercial use of ancient sites.																																	Imagine how I feel being here shooting a movie ... I cant believe things like this can happen to me, Vardalos said late yesterday.																																	Released in 2002, My Big Fat Greek Wedding was a surprise international hit and earned Vardalos an Oscar nomination. 
